ACCESSIBILITY RESOURCES

- The British Geophysical Association's accessible meeting guide: https://geophysics.org.uk/bga-accessible-meeting-guide/ | https://geophysics.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/bga_edi_meeting_checklist.pdf
- The British Geophysical Association's accompanying accessible conference talks and posters guide: https://geophysics.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/accessible_conference_talks_posters.pdf

- Oxford University's inclusive conference guide: https://www.geog.ox.ac.uk/sites/default/files/2023-07/190522_Inclusive_Conference_Guide.pdf

- "What we mean when we talk about accessibility" (by Alistair Duggin for the "Accessibility in government" blog): https://accessibility.blog.gov.uk/2016/05/16/what-we-mean-when-we-talk-about-accessibility-2/

- SeeWriteHear's resources and educational content: https://www.seewritehear.com/learn/ (SeeWriteHear are an organisation who "specialize in innovative technology solutions to help you meet and maintain usability compliance in your content and environments.") 

- Harvard's glossary of DIB (diversity, inclusion and belonging) terms: https://edib.harvard.edu/files/dib/files/dib_glossary.pdf

- The IOP's Diveristy and Inclusion strategy document: https://www.iop.org/about/IOP-diversity-inclusion
- The IOP's LGBT+ Physical Sciences Network page: https://www.iop.org/about/iop-diversity-inclusion/LGBT-physical-sciences-network and email address: LGBTPhysAstro@iop.org

- Perceptually uniform colour maps: https://colorcet.com/ | https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-020-19160-7

- Nina Tame's advocacy work: https://ninatame.komi.io/
